If the defendant description is only one line, then make the attention checks similar. They really stand out they way they are now.

There's information that would be very useful in predicting how likely they are to be arrested that wasn't given, including many factors that don't effect likelihood of committing a crime but do effect the odds of arrest (yes, Race, not to mention political beliefs). I also noticed that several of the defendants had "involved in an abusive romantic relationship" but it was not specified if they were the abuser or the victim.

I also noticed that all the defendants were female. Females are far less likely to get arrested in the first place than males (again, regardless of guilt or likelihood to commit the crime), because of sexism.
